Predict
=======

I noticed a lot of chess players who prepare themselves for the Belgian Interteam Competition.
They download the results of previous rounds, create a table and look up the games of the possible opponents.

This script does the hard work, by downloading the results, parsing the html pages, and preparing the tables.


Usage:
------

python predict_nic.py -c <club number>

The output will be something like this:


    TEAM 1:
        111211             PEEK MAURICE (2391) ( 3.5 / 6)
        ---1--             AKESSON RALF (2469) ( 0.5 / 1)
        22233-          TONOLI BENJAMIN (2211) ( 3.5 / 5)
        ----23             LEUNIS GEERT (2294) ( 1.5 / 2)
        -----2           VERMEULEN BRAM (2298) ( 0.5 / 1)
        333444            GOOSSENS ROEL (2153) ( 4.0 / 6)
        44-555           VAN ESPEN EDDY (2133) ( 1.0 / 5)
        554666          VERHEYDEN JONAS (2129) ( 3.0 / 6)
        665777       OLIVA OLAVE CARLOS (2118) ( 3.5 / 6)
        -76---              WEILER MARC (2073) (   2 / 2)
        78-888       DELANOEIJE PATRICK (2037) ( 2.5 / 5)
        --7---          VAN NOTEN STIJN (1858) ( 0.5 / 5)
        8-----           VAN PRAAG BART (1843) ( 2.0 / 4)
        --8---                CUYT SVEN (1694) ( 2.0 / 5)
    TEAM 2:
        ...




Warning:
--------
It's not idiot proof.



have fun,

Romain.


